                                "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                                "subject": "Inspiration"
                            },
                            "text": "Melusine is a female freshwater spirit from European folklore, often found in a holy well or river. She is usually depicted as a half-woman, half-serpent (or fish in some depictions), and she is sometimes given wings, two tails, or both. Legends about her are often connected with the northern and western regions of France, Luxembourg and the Netherlands. A major theme in the tales about her involves keeping one's promises."
                        },
